commit_message:
Make lock blocking with no time out by default

The lock_timeout option that has been copied from memcached actually
does not mean the same thing at all. In memcached, it's used to expire
the lock when a client dies, whereas in IPC and ZK it's meant to be a
timeout on acquire().
This means that by default acquire(blocking=True) will have different
behaviours between the different drivers.

We now avoid that by removing lock_timeout from ZK and IPC, and allowing
the blocking argument from acquire() to be a numeric value.

Change-Id: Idb68e2ff945403f7ee24d86ea480531122b19ff8

commit_message:
Enabled mask_password to handle byte code strings

Byte code strings passed into mask_password cause the coersion to
six.text_type to fail with a UnicodeDecodeError.  The code can
work with the byte code string, but the incoming message may be
an i18n object that has to be coerced.

The temporary fix is to ignore the UnicodeDecodeError on the
coersion.   A better solution will be provided for Kilo.

This is related to cinder bug #1368527

Change-Id: I6dd5195d004477f61cc87bf22f3bf5958c78f754
Closes-bug: #1366189
Closes-bug: #1368527
(cherry picked from commit 1131b5679fcf1492e5191defd9343b75b7091634)

commit_message:
Use UTF-8 as charset for HTML pages

According to the W3C validator UTF-8 should be used instead of utf8.

---snip---
Rare or unregistered character encoding detected

The character encoding declared for this document (utf8) is supported by the
validator, but may not be widely supported across platforms. For the sake of
interoperability, it is best to use a unicode character encoding such as UTF-8,
or one of the registered character encodings.
---snap---

Change-Id: Ife1862c7c245ee610a7a4d820f9717626e56244c

commit_message:
Rename validate-json target as pep8 and improve it

When discussing with the infra guys they have mentioned it would be
easier to call our linting job pep8, it's indeed badly named but that
target has been used all over openstack for linting projects. As a bonus
point it would make things easier to add the job to the gate. To make
that patch much more interesting than a three characters change I have
improved the validate-samples script to detect if jsonlint was present
and if not fallback to the standard python -mjson.tool which give you
less details but nonetheless works if jsonlint is present.

Change-Id: I8d71a229917004dfd7223a16e4f270101cf2f0a8

commit_message:
Add rpc_workers for neutron-server

Number of separate RPC worker processes to spawn.
 The default, 0, runs the worker thread in the current process.
 Greater than 0 launches that number of child processes as workers.
 The parent process manages them.

Closes-bug: #1340316

Change-Id: I7218390a90b4ad082471900cbf2e9f32a88abe28

[{'created': '2014-10-03 09:29:51.000000000', 'message': "Add validate-json tox target

This is a simple JSON validation script based on python internal json
library. It doesn't give you an output at where the error is but would
at least tell you if that file was good or not. Presumably people would
use something like http://jsonlint.com/ to pinpoint the error.

Change-Id: I930908336deef7daeaab5b55ba2031c64698d880
Implements: blueprint json-validation-gate
"}, {'created': '2014-10-03 09:59:43.000000000', 'message': 'Add validate-json tox target

This is a simple JSON validation script based on demjson python library,
we do some shell script trickeries to exit properly if there is a
failure for tox (should probably patch demjson to properly exit
instead).

Change-Id: I930908336deef7daeaab5b55ba2031c64698d880
Implements: blueprint json-validation-gate
'}]
commit_message:
Add validate-json tox target

This is a simple JSON validation script based on demjson python library,
we do some shell script trickeries to exit properly if there is a
failure for tox (should probably patch demjson to properly exit
instead).

Change-Id: I930908336deef7daeaab5b55ba2031c64698d880
Implements: blueprint json-validation-gate

commit_message:
Add OSSN-0028 - Nova leaks hypervisor host SMBIOS serial number to guests

This add a new OSSN about the SMBIOS serial number of the underlying
compute node hardware being leaked to guest instances.

Closes-bug: #1337349
Change-Id: I724c4117b6ecf28db06b9d601e29e789ac6d2bff

After thinking about this change some, I'm not convinced this would work correctly with multiple threads calling this code. The _cli variable you declare is class scoped, so it will be shared among all created instances of IronicClientWrapper. What if one thread makes a client call, there's a context switch to another thread, and the other thread needs to make a client call?

This may be the reason the other clients I've seen (and based this code off of) have not implemented some sort of caching.

Happy to be proven wrong here, and I'll change my vote, b/c otherwise it looks good."}, {'account_id': 6773, 'date': '2014-07-10 08:20:00.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6: Code-Review-1

So this will work-ish but I have several concerns.

Firstly, the complexity around predicting token expiry is not needed - we have to handle usage of old tokens no matter what, and the few wasted calls this would save don't matter IMO.

Secondly, other folk will want an Ironic client that doesn't need recreation when tokens have been expired/revoked. So all the caching logic etc belongs in python-ironicclient, not in the nova virt driver."}, {'account_id': 5805, 'date': '2014-07-17 00:12:29.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 9: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)

I don't feel just checking that the expiry time is > x seconds is a valid check. However if this is the best method it should at minimum be a settable number of seconds and not hard coded."}, {'account_id': 8125, 'date': '2014-07-17 03:15:24.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 9:

(4 comments)

Thanks for the reviews Chris and Robert!

@lifeless: So you would prefer that when the client object is accessed, we check token expiry, and if it's expired go get a new one?  The only difference is checking utcnow() compared with utcnow()+N seconds.

@lifeless: As for the second point of handling all caching in python-ironicclient, there's an argument to be made for that, however on looking at it I went this way because there might be a desire to have different authentication handling in the ironicclient vs ironic vs anyone else who might like to use ironicclient programatically.

@NobodyCam: I've added a config value for the expiry timeout, although if we simply check for expiry as per lifeless' suggestion, this would go away."}, {'account_id': 8125, 'date': '2014-07-17 03:58:11.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 10.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-07-17 03:58:12.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 10:

http://status.openstack.org/zuul/'}, {'account_id': 4190, 'date': '2014-07-17 04:03:51.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 10: Code-Review-1

No, I'm saying handle *errors* by requesting a new token. You cannot ever tell if your token is valid, because keystone can throw them away anytime, so you have to handle this by catching the exception and resubmitting. This should be ironicclient.

I don't buy your argument, I've seen this exact antipattern with novaclient and heatclient and its why we have such difficulty with openstackclient. There's no good reason not to make the client excellent. I still have concerns about this implementation. Although the class singleton protects the client, I don't believe that network communication is going to work properly. I see two possible scenarios:

1) Communication on the single communication socket IS NOT serialized, thus leading to a potential problem of reading incorrect responses off the wire. Since there can be a thread context switch between sending requests and reading responses, I think we'd have a problem on threads possibly reading data off the wire in the wrong order.

2) Communication on the single communication socket IS serialized (this is the default when using eventlet and monkey patching: http://eventlet.net/doc/basic_usage.html#eventlet.monkey_patch), which leads to requests to nova now being serialized as well."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-07-21 20:59:21.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 11: -Verified

commit_message:
Ironic nova driver to cache ironic client calls

When the nova ironic driver makes ironic client calls, it
currently gets a brand new client for each call.  This patch
caches the client, and reuses it for future requests.

Change-Id: I712738d275646d684f8a5221978dd576f636a5c7
Partial-bug: #1308171

commit_message:
Update basic environment content for Juno

I updated basic environment content in the installation guide
for Juno as follows:

1) Restructured and clarified OpenStack package procedures.
2) Removed RHEL/CentOS 6.5 special cases and workarounds.
3) Changed RHEL/CentOS to use systemd.
4) Improved SLES/openSUSE sysv/systemd steps.
5) Clarified firewall/security content.
6) Indicated that rebooting is necessary to activate network
   changes on Ubuntu and Debian.
7) Removed Python MySQL library from non-controller nodes
   because the services running on them no longer directly
   interact with the database. I'm looking at you,
   nova-network.
8) Other minor fixes.

Change-Id: If95e6b42e596f55c6a66f2d9ab456b335d3098ca
Implements: blueprint installation-guide-improvements
Closes-Bug: #1373821

commit_message:
Add first reliability enforcement

This patch adds an reliability enforcement for mongodb's driver. It
forces deployers to use replicasets or mongos as a mongodb cluster for
Zaqar. In addition to that, it forces deployers to provide a write
concern > 2 and/or majority.

If none of this are met, the driver will raise a RuntimeException and
fail to start. If no write concern is provided, majority will be used.

Change-Id: Ie74a4b441654243b3ed7e7fd6c40863969cd446d
Closes-bug: #1372335

commit_message:
Fixed cinder check for non-admin user

It could happen that user doesn't have privileges to perform
list_services. Sahara should use admin user for that.

Refactored keystone client creation to give admin user
access to keystone via API v2.

Change-Id: I275fa07a02f4729f2fc20fcd1f0ea65f3c4d50b2
Closes-Bug: #1375806
Closes-Bug: #1376336

commit_message:
support TRACE_FAILONLY env variable

In order to get similar behavior to the way testr out of the box
works, only displaying failing results, all the user to define
TRACE_FAILONLY environment variable (any value will do). After this
point only failures, and things leaking out of stderr will end up on
the screen.

We also need to remove the suppression of the inline fail dumps for
this to have the impact that you'd expect.

Change-Id: I72911adc8a03450522429c52db661ec0a1bc4678

commit_message:
Fix Docstrings for test_server_basic_ops.py

In commit I80d785bb5b325ccfac3c5cfd9d076718cf587e80,
Pause/unpause & Suspend/resume tests have been moved from this
test class but docstring was not updated.

Closes-Bug: #1353814

subject: Keystone: Do a service and endpoint create
messages:
[{'account_id': 2834, 'date': '2014-10-03 01:12:38.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-10-03 01:12:56.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Verified+1

Build succeeded.

- noop http://logs.openstack.org/44/125844/1/check/noop/850dd7d : SUCCESS'}, {'account_id': 8745, 'date': '2014-10-03 01:25:52.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

These changes aren't going to work, because they end up setting the keystone endpoints to 127.0.0.1 (which will not be accessible from other pods).

This might be a question for the kubernetes folks: you can start the keystone *services* first, which gets you the service environment variables (like KEYSTONEMASTER_5000_PORT_5000_TCP_ADDR), but these are possibly only valid from the perspective of the current container.  But maybe they are actually useful in general.

I think we need to get this question answered before we can create useful endpoints."}, {'account_id': 8745, 'date': '2014-10-03 01:43:35.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

So, to summarize a conversation I just had on #google-containers:

- Accessing the proxy address of "minion A" from a pod on "minion B" will work *right now*, but will in the near future stop working.

- Kubernetes does not have any way of managing "externally visible" ip addresses, either.

- There is no good way to handle the keystone service catalog.'}, {'account_id': 8745, 'date': '2014-10-03 02:40:27.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Also: we need to make sure that our keystone catalog operations are idempotent...so before creating users/tenants/services/endpoints, we need to check if they exist (or not) first and respond appropriately.  I think radez (?) is looking to see if the os-cloud-config tool can make this easier for us.'}, {'account_id': 2834, 'date': '2014-10-03 05:42:23.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-10-03 05:42:25.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified+1

Build succeeded.

- noop http://logs.openstack.org/44/125844/2/check/noop/cc355fd : SUCCESS'}, {'account_id': 2834, 'date': '2014-10-03 05:50:35.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Just trying to get dev unblocked.  Clearly we should remove sleeps and handle idempotent operations.  I'll file bugs for those issues so we can follow up later.

Apparently services *must* be started prior to pods for kubernetes not to blow up in some circumstances.  We need to change the documentation accordingly.

I'm unclear as to why the minion to minion communication would be disabled.  What argument was offered for a rationale?  OpenStack will require inter-minion communication for most services to operate.

I imagine an inter-k8s communication mechanism will be a common requirement for folks implementing containerized applications since those apps may want to communicate over the k8s network.

Regards
-steve"}, {'account_id': 2834, 'date': '2014-10-03 13:38:51.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-10-03 13:38:52.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Verified+1

Build succeeded.

- noop http://logs.openstack.org/44/125844/3/check/noop/f6e1eb1 : SUCCESS'}, {'account_id': 5792, 'date': '2014-10-03 15:05:30.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

os-cloud-config won't work in icehouse only in juno We can't rely on it until we build our containers with versions that are compatible with the scripts... see notes on https://blueprints.launchpad.net/kolla/+spec/os-cloud-config-in-base"}, {'account_id': 5792, 'date': '2014-10-03 15:22:45.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review+2

I think for the current state of things this is a good move forward, we need to manually pass the ip address for the endpoint in the env vars but hopefully a better solution will be developed that we can swap that out for once it actually exists'}, {'account_id': 2834, 'date': '2014-10-03 15:58:42.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

actually the env vars are automatically passed because they are created when the service is registered.'}, {'account_id': 10419, 'date': '2014-10-03 16:48:08.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-10-03 16:48:14.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: -Verified

Starting gate jobs.

Build succeeded.

commit_message:
Keystone: Do a service and endpoint create

This patch does a service and endpoint create so that each separate service
can find keystone.  This patch also makes the sleeping a bit more logical
although there are TODOs in this area to remove the sleep operations.

Change-Id: Icfee464f9473686da89bfa8b2106172cbfd4c1a8
Closes-Bug: #1376975

commit_message:
VMware: Fix deletion of an instance with no files

When a managed object doesn't contain a property, RetrievePropertiesEx
doesn't return None; it doesn't return the property at all. We were
testing for this incorrectly and not handling it in the code.

Change-Id: I77a0ba4eb5a6cc6075db9c67294f30abaa0e474d

commit_message:
Implement missing get_vif* methods to neutronv2 api

This patch implements methods get_vifs_by_instance() and
get_vif_by_mac_address().

There is potential problem because get_vif_by_mac_address() isn't
limited on other resource like network_id. If there will be two same mac
addresses in different subnets, only the first one will be returned.

Closes-Bug: #1269061
Closes-Bug: #1269062

Change-Id: I7efc9a120cd2748623ba8ae2e27fa7acc44beaf7

Hi Emilien,

Which version of VNX Direct Driver are you targeting at?

In latest driver, VNX Direct Driver (4.1.0 in Juno) also support the following conf options

storage_vnx_authentication_type

storage_vnx_security_file_dir

san_secondary_ip

destroy_empty_storage_group

iscsi_initiators

initiator_auto_registration


Both FC and iSCSI are introduced

cinder.volume.drivers.emc.emc_cli_iscsi.EMCCLIISCSIDriver support iSCSI

cinder.volume.drivers.emc.emc_cli_fc.EMCCLIFCDriver


And iscsi_ip_address has been deprecated since VNX Direct Driver 3.0.0.

Thanks,

Jeegn'}, {'account_id': 3153, 'date': '2014-09-29 02:55:17.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

commit_message:
EMC VNX backend support

Add support for EMC VNX direct driver.

- Create the volume driver for EMC VNX direct driver
- Create the backend for volume type support (multi-backend)
- Unit test for basic parameters

Official documentation used:
http://docs.openstack.org/trunk/config-reference/content/emc-vnx-direct-driver.html

Change-Id: Iccaea371751aac92b6d0df2011e18fd9bd6b98e9

'}]
commit_message:
Revert "Install static element files"

Needs more thought about how to ensure files are owned by the correct user. The only way which occurs to me is a manifest file and I'm not sure that fits within the "convenience budget" compared to installing files with install.d scripts.

This reverts commit 00b7e98af1e8b7f14895736e4df079757624948e.

Change-Id: Iebda1df225471b45b17f922b9e3c2e2d487bdffb

commit_message:
Initial libvirt and nova-compute structure

This lays the groundwork for the docker compute container.

The compute node is composed of libvirt container and a nove-compute
container.  We are going to have to sort out how to get k8s to schedule
this pod 1 per node.

Change-Id: I1e06e4b5f5bde83b582edfc1094084a4ee353371
Partial-blueprint: kube-libvirt-container
Partial-blueprint: kube-nova-container

commit_message:
coordination: remove destroy() from the lock protocol

This is remove the need to manually destroy the lock, especially in the
IPC driver. It's very complicated to know when we can destroy a lock, so
what we do is that we destroy it when releasing, and make the rest of
the code solid so it handles lock being destroyed under its feet.

Change-Id: I67eab4e403b0d3194cf8b082a3059ef4536c3988

commit_message:
Add in concept of project priorities

* Add section in kilo-template about project priorities (with a link to
  the kilo priorities document)
* Add in kilo priorities page. Currently this list is empty and we hope
  to fill it out at the summit
* Add the yaml file of priority blueprints that are ready for review.
  This is where we will track which priority blueprints need review.

Change-Id: I339e88f8055a63a9a9423d997da6581f977428c9

commit_message:
Explicitly require a Use Cases section for Kilo

We should put more stress on making it easy to figure out what the use
case is for every blueprint.  All blueprints should have a use case for
someone.

Related to: I7075a130c01be22f3ee5315d4a65b8e524b5a1ad

Change-Id: I7f378054b52488e6347304d3894868caa234b4fd

fix mariadb Dockerfile

- fix base image
- expose ports

commit_message:
Fix DISTRO_NAME usage for centos7 element

In each of the changed files in this patch, the $DISTRO_NAME usage
is checking against "centos".  The valid value for the centos7
element for $DISTRO_NAME is "centos7"[1].

[1] http://git.io/8IvuTw

Change-Id: I5d59e195c38fc7ff5b3235e195171fafcf5b4f87

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-10-03 12:50:24.000000000', 'message': 'Make suspended/paused VMs hard-rebootable.

Commit a69251804e62f871f93ffa420978f9b61a36df9c "Relax API
restrictions around the use of reboot" looks imcomplete because
@check_instance_state() of nova.compute.api.API.reboot() allows
instances with task_state=RESUMING/UNPAUSING/PAUSING/SUSPENDING
but instance.save() doesn't care them at expected_task_state.
This patch completes them.

Change-Id: Ia668bbb79691b8647f399e1cb485cb11877363de
Closes-Bug: 1377138
'}]
commit_message:
Make suspended/paused VMs hard-rebootable.

Commit a69251804e62f871f93ffa420978f9b61a36df9c "Relax API
restrictions around the use of reboot" looks imcomplete because
@check_instance_state() of nova.compute.api.API.reboot() allows
instances with task_state=RESUMING/UNPAUSING/PAUSING/SUSPENDING
but instance.save() doesn't care them at expected_task_state.
This patch completes them.

Change-Id: Ia668bbb79691b8647f399e1cb485cb11877363de
Closes-Bug: 1377138

commit_message:
Don't stop screens in upgrade-*

Stopping things is the job of stop-base.

upgrade-horizon is somewhat special in this case because stop-base
does nothing with it, so just to be sure it continues to stop but
uses screen_stop instead.

In the process remove direct references to calling 'screen' which
allows USE_SCREEN=False to work without 'screen' being unable to
find screens.

Change-Id: I7cf36feee0006c86f39c00b695adf049b87a1251

Multi backend attepts to read a deleted domain

This effectively results in all delete-domain requests failing when
the multi backend is used.

Closes-Bug: 1375397

commit_message:
Fix heat purge deleted cron job

The cron job was sending errors to root's mailbox. Errors are
now directed to syslog.

The job couldn't find heat-manage. Added PATH and included
/usr/local/bin where heat-manage is located.

Change-Id: I31f28ac741731018d5be7943d0a336c99a909562
Closes-Bug: 1369755

Universal is used to identify pure-Python module(by bdist_wheel).
For these, it is sufficient to build a wheel with _any_ Python ABI
version and publish that to PyPI (by whatever means).

Change-Id: I40d66609277e58e8d6fee9cc98948f7b2507f75a
'}]
commit_message:
Mark glance_store as being a universal wheel

Universal is used to identify pure-Python module(by bdist_wheel).
For these, it is sufficient to build a wheel with _any_ Python ABI
version and publish that to PyPI (by whatever means).

Change-Id: I40d66609277e58e8d6fee9cc98948f7b2507f75a

commit_message:
Versioned API endpoint

Glance now has a v2 API available, but the current puppet module
only sets up the v1 endpoint. This change allows an operator to
specify a v2 endpoint, and have keystone set up the catalog.

Change-Id: I99ed8dd22cf1f0457773145204305c221abc2b52

commit_message:
Versioned endpoint support

Glance now has both v1 and v2 API versions, but the endpoint
created with this module only creates a v1 endpoint. This change
allows an operator to specify v2 endpoint and have keystone set
it up accordingly.

Change-Id: I61d9ab35e4972d82b0d3f87471f4fbe8a56ad90e

[{'created': '2014-07-29 16:34:48.000000000', 'message': 'Install static element files with oac

Several elements want to install static files. Some do this using the
"os-apply-config" directory, which means these files are unnecessarily
rewritten every time os-refresh-config triggers. Others put files in a
"files" dir and install them from the install.d script.

This patch makes both these suboptimal approaches unnecessary by
offering elements a "static" directory. Files placed in here will be
copied using os-apply-config into the image.

Using oac for this over rsync means that when control files are added
(I8fe7126d7261c1f106d7413bd31aa379e9ae5c3e), we can easily create
symlinks, control the mode etc. It also opens the door for build-time
metadata to control the content, although I don't know if this is needed
by anyone.

Change-Id: I61276a1fc71f0bdfd90134b000100e5e64b1ff75

Install static element files

Several elements want to install static files. Some do this using the
"os-apply-config" directory, which means these files are unnecessarily
rewritten every time os-refresh-config triggers. Others put files in a
"files" dir and manually script the installation from an install.d
script.

This patch offers a more convenient "static" directory. Files placed in
here will be rsynced into the image.

Change-Id: I61276a1fc71f0bdfd90134b000100e5e64b1ff75

commit_message:
Determines version from auth_url when not explicit

This changes the default version to None instead
of '3', and grabs the version from the auth_url.
Before, passing it only a v2 auth_url would break
with no good explanation.

Change-Id: I97b22ee9b978c34e98c220441fbea940b76e8e5f
Co-Authored-By: Telles Mota Vidal Nbrega <tellesmvn@lsd.ufcg.edu.br>
Closes-Bug: 1357109

[{'created': '2014-10-03 11:06:46.000000000', 'message': 'labs: add Vagrant key to basedisk

Add the Vagrant insecure public key to the base disk.

For installs over ssh, the public key is already installed by preseed
(or kickstart). For installs over a VirtualBox shared directory, the key
is currently only cached (in lib/vagrant-ssh-keys); a cluster build
without a key in the cache requires an Internet connection -- something
we want to avoid.

Leaving the script in config/scripts.* for the node VMs keeps base disks
built without this change working.

Change-Id: Ic43f8e4809bbf6719e0d404c394c354d6f623449
'}]
commit_message:
labs: add Vagrant key to basedisk

Add the Vagrant insecure public key to the base disk.

For installs over ssh, the public key is already installed by preseed
(or kickstart). For installs over a VirtualBox shared directory, the key
is currently only cached (in lib/vagrant-ssh-keys); a cluster build
without a key in the cache requires an Internet connection -- something
we want to avoid.

Leaving the script in config/scripts.* for the node VMs keeps base disks
built without this change working.

Change-Id: Ic43f8e4809bbf6719e0d404c394c354d6f623449

commit_message:
Catch IOError in cliutils

Catch always IOError in cliutils main method.
This simplifes output for end user and make it simpler to undrestand
that user specified wrong file.

Change-Id: I2e3bc7a9b5daff00c62ddf645fc2aaccae20f27b

commit_message:
Install openstack-selinux on RHEL

The openstack-selinux package contains policy updates for OpenStack.
Updates are accrued in openstack-selinux before they are merged into
the upstream selinux-policy package.

Change-Id: I7c00e5cae17489202fe7aee3e656fca27ab630ba

isolate event storage models

move event storage models to event module. this is the first step
to separating metering and event data.

Change-Id: I6d720690a958f5b3accf22db66c830bfa48ed9ae
Partially-Implements: blueprint dedicated-event-db

commit_message:
labs: rewrite enable_vagrant_ssh_keys.sh

Split the code into two functions:

get_vagrant_key: download a Vagrant insecure key (if necessary) and copy
it to ~/.ssh.

authorize_vagrant_key: authorize a Vagrant insecure key for logins into
the VM.

Change-Id: Id420aa14a48aac9e9c2814e0b4cdcbded90f0560

Instance, Restart Instance, Delete User, Delete Database,
and Delete Backup actions.

commit_message:
Use host information passed while starting service

While starting the heat engine service, the host parameter value
being passed to EngineService should be used instead of referring
the conf.
Similarly in the case of EngineListener.

Change-Id: I365f7e21637776d2e7da7685790758f3dcd06989

commit_message:
add fix for testing data processing tab in horizon

Since sahara plugin fully integrated with the horizon,
in ui tests should be changed URLs of responces.
closes-bug: #1376482

commit_message:
Improve error for custom resource

Improve error for case when custom template resource specified via http
or https url. Same behaviour is presented for python-heatclent.

Change-Id: I05c6bad3e6a52ca041fd8a51849ff4e6af23baed
Closes-Bug: #1376656

commit_message:
Remove kombu as a dependency for Ironic

It was required before oslo.messaging now kombu is not used anymore in
our code database.

Change-Id: If9c52c4fce52b913e404cd41a81d187986041df0

commit_message:
Use strings of 8 chars for indexing Swift chunks.

This change makes Freezer compatibile with the streaming of files
splitted in more than 10 chunks.

Change-Id: I7084a4fb9f3e724d6581c45cebff523deaa7f4f7
Closes-Bug: #1376497

commit_message:
Included info about Federated Identity

Updated the Security guide to include information about the overview of
Federated identity, the terms used and how Identity Service handles mapping of SAML
assertions to assigned roles.
Also included some steps for configuring Identity Service for federation.
Partial-Bug: #1319158

Change-Id: I0d0307f26935d4e5d09ea00d0f95f7e41dbfdb50

commit_message:
Install dib from pip

diskimage-builder makes releases to PyPI and is not part of the
integrated release. Since it's not, we don't need to consume its
master branch - rather, we can consume its releases.

Change-Id: If9297a28604612140c39dfe44e77107d1372f0bb

commit_message:
Bump BUILD_TIMEOUT for both Ironic drivers

BUILD_TIMEOUT is currently bumped from its default 196s to
300s for the Ironic agent_ssh deploy driver.  Enabling parallel
Tempest testing of the pxe_ssh fails periodically due to build
timeouts, likely due to concurrent deployments generating lots of
i/o.  This bumps the timeout for all Ironic jobs.

Change-Id: I638aa18c77d7a60e03df7bb8039dbd532cafa7ab

commit_message:
Add 'python-six' dependency to nailgun package

Nailgun package had missing requirement for 'python-six' which was
causing usage of 'python-six' package in version that do not have
all required features.

Change-Id: Ieb9b18923fd6d797da09044c6a48f9228b64e910

commit_message:
Add missing 'six' dependency to nailgun

Due to the missing entry for 'six' in requirements.txt for nailgun
in some cases old version of six was used (from other packages) which
was causes issues with missing features in older version of six.

Now this dependency has been added.

Change-Id: Ib44dbd02e6d775ca269460d836d9a2c354513e3b
Closes-Bug: #1366728

commit_message:
Partial revert of bug/1372428 commit

There was no need to change default parameter in class definition
in I636125c7b4b092e108c584cc02c3d4177cc6a7c0

Changing parameter in class declaration in openstack::ceilometer
is enough.

Change-Id: Idcadfa1f213978193e82b15bb092e06f3aa3299f

[{'created': '2014-09-02 07:09:34.000000000', 'message': 'nova-api should not inform nova-sync-db

The definition for nova-sync-db shows a dependency on nova-api.
However, starting the API has a risk of objects being created
before the DB sync can run. The dependency should be the reverse
to make sure the DB migration is complete before the API is started.

Related-Bug: #1335804
Change-Id: I7ba5129b43529183a34c8791f28696ee53b1bbec

commit_message:
nova-api should not inform nova-sync-db

The definition for nova-sync-db shows a dependency on nova-api.
However, starting the API has a risk of objects being created
before the DB sync can run. There should be a dependency to
to make sure the DB migration is complete before the API is started.

Related-Bug: #1335804
Change-Id: I7ba5129b43529183a34c8791f28696ee53b1bbec

commit_message:
IPC: fix a potential race condition at init

It's possible that between the moment the code tries to get the
semaphore it has been destroyed, so let's try in a loop to catch it
until we succeed.

Change-Id: I853a7262ebd94ec954f4fb923e7547c8fd7841b4
